article.description: — Kobi Nwandu had 18 points as Niagara narrowly beat Quinnipiac 59-56 on Friday.
article.headline: Nwandu scores 18 to carry Niagara over Quinnipiac 59-56
article.linkText: Nwandu scores 18 to carry Niagara over Quinnipiac 59-56
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- — Kobi Nwandu had 18 points as Niagara narrowly beat Quinnipiac 59-56 on Friday. Marcus Hammond had 12 points and nine rebounds for Niagara (6-7, 5-6 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Greg Kuakumensah added nine rebounds and three blocks, and Nicholas Kratholm had 13 rebounds. Kratholm made 1 of 2 free throws with eight seconds left for a three-point lead and Tyrese Williams missed a 3-pointer at the other end. Williams had 13 points and seven rebounds for the Bobcats (3-6, 1-4), who have now lost four straight. Jacob Rigoni added 12 points and Tymu Chenery had seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
